# MCP Merge Response Schema and Examples

## When You Need This

When harness returns `nextAction: "agent_call_mcp_merge_retrieval_results"` and you need to submit the consolidated knowledge from MCP retrieval.

---

## Complete Merge Response Schema

```json
{
  "task_id": "from-mcp-response-task_id",
  "merged": {
    "decisions": [
      {"knowledge_item_id": "dec-001", "title": "Decision title", "summary": "What decision was made"}
    ],
    "best_practices": [
      {"knowledge_item_id": "bp-001", "title": "Practice title", "summary": "What is the best practice"}
    ],
    "anti_patterns": [
      {"knowledge_item_id": "ap-001", "title": "Anti-pattern title", "summary": "What to avoid"}
    ],
    "similar_cases": [
      {"knowledge_item_id": "sc-001", "title": "Case title", "summary": "Similar situation"}
    ],
    "constraints": [
      {"knowledge_item_id": "con-001", "title": "Constraint", "summary": "Hard requirement"}
    ],
    "references": [
      {"knowledge_item_id": "ref-001", "title": "Reference", "summary": "Code location or commit"}
    ],
    "structures": [
      {"knowledge_item_id": "str-001", "title": "Structure", "summary": "Data structure or pattern"}
    ]
  }
}
```

## Required Fields

- `task_id` - Same as from MCP response
- `merged` - Must contain ALL 7 buckets (even if empty arrays)
  - `decisions` - Key decisions discovered
  - `best_practices` - Proven approaches
  - `anti_patterns` - Things to avoid
  - `similar_cases` - Related implementations
  - `constraints` - Hard requirements
  - `references` - Code pointers
  - `structures` - System components

Each item must have: `knowledge_item_id`, `title`, `summary`

